headline: SoftBank Says It Sold Its Entire Nvidia Stake. The Chip Stock is Sliding.
summary: The Japanese company in a Tuesday statement said it sold 32 million shares of chip giant Nvidia, a "complete sale," in October, raising nearly $6 billion.

headline: T-Mobile US, Inc. to Present at the Wells Fargo TMT Summit
summary: BELLEVUE, Wash., November 11, 2025--Jon Freier, president of the consumer group of T-Mobile US, Inc. (NASDAQ: TMUS), will present and provide a business update on Tuesday, November 18, 2025 at 3:00 p.m. Pacific Time (PT) at the Wells Fargo 9th Annual TMT Summit.

headline: Nvidia shares dip 2% after SoftBank sells entire stake in AI chip darling

headline: Does TDS’s Expanded Buyback Highlight a New Chapter in Fiber and Tower Strategy?
summary: In recent days, Telephone and Data Systems, Inc. announced an additional US$500 million increase to its share repurchase authorization, bringing the total buyback potential to US$750 million, and provided key updates on ongoing transformation initiatives including advancements in fiber and tower operations following the sale of its wireless business to T-Mobile. This move reflects management's increased confidence in long-term value creation as the company sharpens its focus on fiber...
